===Noun===
'''gerund'''
#(''grammar''): a verbal form that ends with the suffix ''-ing'' and functions as a noun. (In English, a gerund has the same spelling as a [[present participle]], but functions differently)
#:Example:  '''''Walking''' is good exercise.''
#(''grammar''): In some languages, such as Italian or Russian, a verbal form similar to a present participle, but functioning as an adverb.
#:Example: ''Нельзя переходить улицу '''читая''' газету.'' (One shouldn't cross a street '''reading''' a newspaper.)

